By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – As the number of cases of Covid-19 continues to increase, President Buhari is set to address the country, Monday April 13 7 pm. A statement signed by his Senior Special Assistant Media Femi Adesina directs all media houses to hook up live to the broadcast. The statement reads in full: President Muhammadu Buhari will broadcast to the nation Monday, April 13, 2020 at 7pm. Television, radio and other electronic media outlets are enjoined to hook up to the network services of the Nigerian Television Authority (NTA) and Federal Radio Corporation of Nigeria (FRCN) respectively for the broadcast. Femi Adesina Special Adviser to the President (Media & Publicity) President Muhammadu Buhari will hold a national address today (Monday) by 7pm. This was contained in a statement by Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina. The statement read, “President Muhammadu Buhari will broadcast to the nation Monday, April 13, 2020 at 7pm. “Television, radio and… April 13, 2020 In "News" Agency Reporter Abuja (Sundiata Post) - President Muhammadu Buhari has finally bowed to pressure as will finally address Nigerians by 7pm today (Sunday). His Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, disclosed this in a statement. Many Nigerians have been eager to hear what the President will have to… March 29, 2020 In "Top Stories" Abuja-President Muhammadu Buhari is to speak on current national issues on Wednesday during his maiden Presidential Media Chat. This information is contained in a statement issued in Abuja by the president’s Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Mr Femi Adesina. According to the statement, the media chat will be broadcast… December 29, 2015 In "News"